You won't catch any flak from me. I fully agree with the "all points in
between" on a .009. The .010, .009, and the .050 do what they are supposed
to do, but nothing can replace the gentle curve of the proper vacuum
diaphragm dizzy for your motor. For around town standard driving application
I would swear by the Bosch SVDA vacuum dizzy, even over the factory vacuum
dizzy. Sure, it's pricey, but the couple of extra MPG and the lessened heat
derived wear and tear on your engine makes it worth it.

